properties.headline: NRL - Friday 28 August - MOORE PARK Moore Park Rd, Anzac Pde, Lang Rd, Eastern Distributor approaching The SCG

arrangementAttachments.displayName: Moore Park walking & transport route map
arrangementAttachments.linkName: Moore Park walking & transport route map

properties.otherAdvice:
NRL: Roosters v Broncos at the SCG from 7:55pm until 9:50pm approx.

Traffic may be heavier than usual on Anzac Pde, Eastern Distributor, Moore Park Rd, Cleveland St and Lang Rd approaching Moore Park as fans travel to and from the game during Friday evening peak.

Driver Ave will also be partially closed from approx 5:50pm and remain closed until crowds have safely cleared the precinct after full-time. 

Special event clearways will be in effect on various roads from 3pm until 11pm including sections of Moore Park Rd, Lang Rd, Albion St, Chalmers St, Fitzroy St, Flinders St and Foveaux St. 

Clearways are strict no-parking zones even for local residents and RMS Mobility Scheme Permit holders. Check signs carefully as vehicles left in clearways will be towed and a fee applies.

arrangementElements.html:
Special event clearways are strict no-parking zones even for local residents and RMS Mobility Scheme Parking Permit holders. Check signs carefully as vehicles left in clearways will be towed and a fee applies. If your vehicle is towed, call 132 701 to find its new location.

SURRY HILLS / MOORE PARK

FROM 6AM TO 11PM

  • Cleveland Street between City Road and South Dowling Street

FROM 3PM TO 11PM

  • Albion Street between Mary Street and Flinders Street (northern side)
  • Albion Street between Bourke Street and Flinders Street (southern side)
  • Chalmers Street between Cleveland Street and Devonshire Street (western side)
  • Fitzroy Street between South Dowling Street and Bourke Street (northern side)
  • Flinders Street between Albion Street and Moore Park Road (eastern side)
  • Foveaux Street between Bourke Street and Crown Street (northern side)
  • Lang Road between Cook Road and Anzac Parade (both sides)
  • Moore Park Road between Flinders Street and Driver Avenue (northern side)
  • Moore Park Road between Driver Avenue and Anzac Parade (southern side)

properties.publicTransport: Visit transportnsw.info to plan your trip.
properties.otherAdvice:
NRL: Eels v Rabbitohs at Bankwest Stadium from 7:50pm until 9:35pm approx. 

Traffic may be heavier than usual on O'Connell St, Parramatta Rd, Church St, Victoria Rd and Pennant Hills Rd as fans travel to the stadium during Thursday evening peak.

After the game, as fans leave the stadium and nearby carparks in Parramatta CBD traffic may also be heavy on local roads so allow extra travel time.

Fans driving to game should allow additional time for parking.

properties.headline: Super Rugby - Saturday 29 August - LEICHHARDT Mary Street at Glover Street
properties.publicTransport: Visit transportnsw.info to plan your trip.
properties.otherAdvice:
Super Rugby: Rebels v Waratahs at Leichhardt Oval from 7:15pm until 9pm approx. 

Traffic may be heavier than usual on Mary St, Glover St, Perry St, Lilyfield Rd and Balmain Rd as fans travel to and from the game.

A partial closure of Mary St at the oval will be in place from before the game and remain closed until fans have safely cleared the area. Traffic will be detoured via Chapel St. 

Motorists requiring to access other venues in the Park should use either Maliyawul St or Glover St and allow extra time. 

Fans driving to the game should allow extra travel time for parking and be aware of increased pedestrian activity on local roads.
